HEADWORD: Chetvert
<hw>Chet"vert</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Russ.
<ets>chetverte</ets> one fourth.]</ety> <def>A measure of grain equal to
0.7218 of an imperial quarter, or 5.95 Winchester bushels.</def>
<mark>[Russia]</mark>⟦br⟧
